message:
fix(freeze): Enable multi-arg tail recursion optimization

The tail call codegen already correctly handles multi-arg functions by:
1. Popping all arguments into temporary variables first
2. Then assigning them all to argv

The artificial restriction on arg_count != 1 was unnecessary. Removed
it and improved freeze status logging to show all manifest functions
with their freeze status (will freeze or BLOCKED with reason).

Tested with 3-arg tail-recursive fibonacci:
  function fibTail(n, a, b) {
    if (n === 0) return a;
    if (n === 1) return b;
    return fibTail(n - 1, b, a + b);
  }
  fibTail(35, 0, 1) // => 9227465

